div.stage:
The  Queen  seated in state;
                       near her  Du Croc  and  Murray
                        ;  Darnley  in front, as at his arraignment;
                       on the one side the Lords of the Congregation; on the other those of the
                       Queen's party,  Bothwell, Huntley, Caithness, Athol 
                       , and the Archbishop of St. Andrews.
